node.text:
Hey StarReaders! 😉 ⭐ 
We hope you didn't miss our first & second episode from the Star Stable Master Class with author @helenadahlgrenofficial. Here's the first episode for you to learn from now or save for later, to enjoy during your cozy weekend! 📖

If you've already dived into our Star Stable Master Class, we're happy to let you know that Episodes 3 & 4 will come out soon, stay tuned! 🤩

Not only is this Star Stable Master Class full of awesome advice, but we hope it encourages you to write your own story! Put your learnings to the test by joining our ongoing storytelling challenge. Take part in our short
story competition for the chance to have your story turned into an
Instagram comic by illustrator Elli Puukangaas! @ellipuukangas #SSOStoryTellers #ReadWriteUnite

node.title: Star Stable Master Class: From reader to writer

Guillermo Gadea has returned to Jorvik! Guillermo works for Horses of Jorvik creating fun races for different breeds. Usually, these types of races only feature one breed at a time, but he thought a bunch of horses deserved some love!

You can race with your Friesian/Sport Friesian, Clydesdale, Fjord, Faramawr and Aldrach, Petra and Erinys, or Woodear and Pepita! If you enter the race on another type of horse, you will kindly be asked to return with another. This race is a bit chillier than usual—the Frozen Horse Race is in Dino Valley! #OnceUponADragon

Hey StarFam! ⭐ France's beloved gentle giant, the Percheron, has just arrived in our Star Stable Horses app! In the app, you can raise your very own horse from a foal up to a level 10 horse, ready to hit the Jorvik racing tracks with you as its rider. ✨ When your Percheron reaches level 10 you can transfer it to Star Stable Online for 850 Star Coins. 🐴  #StarStableHorses #PerfectPercherons

Star Stable Horses is available both in the AppStore and in Google Play and is free to download.

P.S. Please remember that it might take some time before the Appstore/Play Store have the update available for each device.

node.text:
The new dragon horses Faramawr and Aldrach mask themselves as Friesians, a breed many consider the most beautiful and regal of them all. It’s easy to see why they chose that breed - their beauty is spellbinding! But as dragons, they love danger. So, maybe hang out with their pets (they like adventure, too, but with less fire involved). 

Get Faramawr’s loyal companion Happandi and Aldrach’s feisty friend Kolandi bundled into 2000 and 5000 Star Coin packages now. Details on our website!

node.text:
Hey StarFam! This week, two magical horses join us in Jorvik and the Riding Hall revamp is unveiled.

★Faramawr the Green embodies prosperity and life thriving after disaster, like the fertile soil and new islands formed in the wake of volcanic eruption. 
★Aldrach the Red is the embodiment of nature's destructive but necessary forces, such as volcanic eruptions. 
Faramawr and Aldrach can be found with Gary Goldtooth at his usual camp in Moorland, close to Old Jasper’s Barn. These fierce horses will join your family for 950 Star Coins each. #OnceUponADragon

Happandi and Kolandi can fly! They would love to discover Jorvik by your side, so for an adoption fee of 400 SC each, they’ll join you as a flying pet!

It's time for the big reveal! The Riding Hall has been under some behind-the-scenes construction, and the remodel is finally complete! Along with a fresh and modern look, we have a ton of improvements for you to enjoy.
Keep on reading at starstable.com to find out more about this week’s update!

Remember when we asked you to take our survey for the special 10th anniversary horse? 🤩 You got to pick everything from horse breed to colors and markings. Well....we've been hard at work behind the scenes and here's the first look - this horse has been created from the results of your wishes. ✨

node.text:
Happy Wednesday, StarFam! We’ve all been waiting, and now it’s time for the return of the beloved trail ride event known as the Red String Trail Ride!

To symbolize the unbreakable bond between friends or a rider and their horse, it’s tradition to follow a trail up in the Firgrove mountains and tie a red string at the end. This tradition is known as the Red String Trail Ride and is a celebrated event amongst Jorvegian riders!

You start the Red String Trail Ride by signing up at the trail ride board to get a red string, and finish the ride by tying the string at the end of the trail!

Keep on reading at starstable.com to find out more about this week’s update

node.text:
Cuteness comes in all sizes and our beloved #JorvikSmoll is no exception! 
We 10/10 recommend this cutie for your #SSOSummer adventures. 😍

Pros: 
⭐ very cute
⭐ compact - could sneak it anywhere
⭐ super fast, legs go vroom

Cons:
⭐ you better have your eyes wide open on the road as this little cutie will mainly be focusing on the grass!
⭐ not waterproof **
** if you cross a lake, their size does not guarantee that you'll stay dry.
